{
  "stem": "4963.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Aliyah Bet was an organization that was formed to get the remaining Eastern European Jews out of Lithuania into Israel-- into Palestine in those days.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was 1945.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And one of my aunts', Hanna, the one who was a dentist, best friend was somebody whose name was Schmuel.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't remember his last name.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was in charge of the Aliyah Bet.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So he was really the one who was organizer-- who was organizing groups of people to go out, underground movement-- it was an underground movement-- to form groups of Jewish people, to get the-- smuggle them out from Lithuania into Poland, where Poland was freer.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was already after the Germans abdicated, so Poland was also under was under Russian, but he was much more liberal.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Poles never somehow gave in as much as the Lithuanians, and so when someone escaped into Poland, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] they were already-- it was easier for them to leave Poland to go out.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The-- the way of escape was from Lithuania to Poland to Germany.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was after VE Day.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was-- when I left Kaunas was in December of 1945.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I can remember-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] it wasn't-- I can't-- I, myself, cannot remember that distinctly.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember hearing about it from other people, reading about it, because we were liberated, you see, in 1944.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we were-- there wasn't that much of a change, because it was-- the Russians were there and the Russians were there again.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So as far as I was concerned, it wasn't too much of a change for me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I remember hearing that, you know, the concentration camps were open.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
